This paper proposes a method for learning Gradient Boosted Decision Trees (GBDTs) for multiple outputs. The paper discusses the use of GBDTs in machine learning, which falls under the category of "cs.LG" (Machine Learning). The proposed method involves considering the correlations between variables, which is a common topic in "cs.AI" (Artificial Intelligence) and "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms). The paper also discusses experiments on real-world datasets, which could fall under "cs.CV" (Computer Vision) or "cs.CL" (Computation and Language).
